## DOC 04 — HLD

**Replace Section 4 entirely — Eligibility Agent Architecture:**

**4. Multi-Agent System Architecture (LangGraph)**

The core AI system is a LangGraph StateGraph with one Orchestrator and 10 specialist agents. All agents share a common GraphState object passed through the graph. Agents communicate via LangGraph message passing — never direct API calls between agents.

**GraphState (shared across all agents):**
```
{
  citizen_id: string,
  session_id: string,
  channel: "web|voice|whatsapp",
  lang: string,
  profile: CitizenProfile,
  messages: Message[],
  intent: string,
  active_schemes: Scheme[],
  reasoning_trace: Step[],
  agent_outputs: {
    eligibility: {},
    discovery: {},
    guidance: {},
    document: {},
    grievance: {},
    financial: {},
    comparison: {},
    csc: {},
    analytics: {}
  }
}
```

**Orchestrator Routing Logic (LangGraph conditional edges):**
```
START
  → intent_classifier node
      → "eligibility_query"   → [Agent1, Agent2] parallel
      → "application_request" → Agent1 → Agent3
      → "grievance"           → Agent5
      → "comparison"          → Agent8
      → "financial_plan"      → Agent7
      → "document_verify"     → Agent4
      → "status_check"        → Spring Boot direct (no agent)
      → "csc_assist"          → Agent9
  → response_composer node
END
```

**Agent 1 — Eligibility Agent (LangGraph ReAct loop):**

Tool registry (6 tools):
- get_profile_field(field) — fetches from shared GraphState profile
- check_scheme_eligibility(scheme_id, profile) — hard rule check, returns pass/fail per criterion
- verify_income_dbt(citizen_id) — cross-checks declared income against DBT transfer records
- check_disability_registry(aadhaar_hash) — verifies disability certificate against UDID registry
- fetch_state_rules(state, scheme_id) — fetches state-specific overrides for Central schemes
- query_similar_outcomes(profile_hash) — finds anonymised outcomes of citizens with similar profiles

ReAct loop: Agent 1 reasons in natural language about which tool to call next. Example autonomous reasoning chain: "Citizen declared income ₹1.8L. Before confirming PM-KISAN eligibility I should verify_income_dbt to cross-check. DBT shows ₹2.1L transfers — above PM-KISAN threshold. Mark ineligible. Now check state-specific override for UP — UP has extended threshold to ₹2.5L. Citizen is eligible under UP override."

**Agent 2 — Discovery Agent (persistent event loop):**

Runs as always-on Cloud Run service (not a job). Has its own LangGraph loop:
```
TRIGGER (PIB RSS new item OR daily cron)
  → fetch_source node (PIB text / MyScheme page / state portal)
  → gemini_extract node (structured eligibility_rules JSON)
  → deduplication_check node (scheme_code hash lookup in MongoDB)
  → upsert_node (insert new / update changed / skip identical)
  → embed_node (Atlas Vector Search, only changed schemes)
  → alert_node (notify admin of new schemes added today)
```
Self-healing: if MyScheme returns 429 or blocks bot, Agent 2 switches to sitemap fallback, logs the block to admin_alerts collection, backs off for 2 hours.

**Agent 3 — Application Guidance Agent (browser-use):**

Domain whitelist (hardcoded, never changeable at runtime):
- *.gov.in domains only
- pgportal.gov.in
- scholarships.gov.in
- pmayg.nic.in
- pmkisan.gov.in

Flow:
```
TRIGGER (citizen selects scheme to apply)
  → portal_navigator (browser-use opens scheme apply URL)
  → form_analyser (identifies all form fields on current page)
  → profile_mapper (maps form fields to citizen_profiles fields)
  → pre_filler (fills mapped fields via browser-use)
  → screenshot_capturer (captures each completed step)
  → checklist_generator (Gemini generates step-by-step guide from screenshots)
  → missing_docs_detector (compares required fields vs profile — flags gaps)
  → output: {checklist, screenshots[], missing_docs[], pre_filled_count}
```

**Agent 4 — Document Verification Agent:**

Extends existing OCR pipeline. After OCR extracts fields:
```
  → document_classifier (income_cert | caste_cert | aadhaar | disability_cert | land_record)
  → date_extractor (issue_date, expiry_date, validity_period)
  → expiry_checker (flag if expired or expiring < 30 days)
  → profile_crosscheck (name, DOB, address vs citizen_profiles)
  → scheme_sufficiency_check (for each target scheme: is this doc type + validity sufficient?)
  → output: {doc_type, is_valid, mismatches[], insufficient_for_schemes[], expires_in_days}
```

**Agent 5 — Grievance Agent (browser-use):**

Domain whitelist: pgportal.gov.in only.
```
  → status_checker (browser-use: opens scheme portal, finds application by externalAppId, returns status)
  → grievance_drafter (Gemini: drafts letter in citizen's language, correct ministry officer, correct format)
  → pgportal_submitter (browser-use: navigates pgportal.gov.in, fills grievance form, submits)
  → reference_storer (saves reference number to applications.grievance_ref)
  → output: {current_status, grievance_submitted, reference_number}
```

**Agent 6 — Proactive Nudge Agent (scheduled):**

Two triggers: daily cron (deadline check) + weekly cron (new schemes check).
```
DAILY:
  → deadline_scanner (schemes with application_deadline within 7 days OR 1 day)
  → eligible_citizen_finder (citizens matching scheme eligibility who haven't applied)
  → rate_limiter (max 2 messages/citizen/week, skip opted-out citizens)
  → whatsapp_sender (Twilio: personalised message in citizen's lang)

WEEKLY:
  → new_scheme_fetcher (schemes added in last 7 days)
  → profile_matcher (which existing citizens newly qualify)
  → rate_limiter
  → whatsapp_sender
```

**Agent 7 — Financial Planning Agent:**
```
  → eligible_scheme_loader (all schemes where eligibility_score > 70)
  → benefit_calculator (sum annual benefit_amount per scheme)
  → payment_calendar_builder (month: [scheme, amount] based on scheme disbursement schedule)
  → effort_ranker (rank by benefit_amount / application_complexity_score)
  → output: {total_annual_benefit, breakdown[], calendar{}, ranked_by_effort[]}
```

**Agent 8 — Scheme Comparison Agent:**
```
  → scheme_fetcher (loads full scheme docs for both scheme IDs)
  → eligibility_diff (compares eligibility_rules field by field)
  → benefit_diff (compares benefit_amount, benefit_type, frequency)
  → process_diff (compares application steps, documents required, portal difficulty)
  → profile_matcher (which scheme fits THIS citizen better and why)
  → localiser (outputs comparison in citizen's detected language)
  → output: {scheme_a, scheme_b, diffs{}, recommendation, reasoning}
```

**Agent 9 — CSC Field Verification Agent:**
```
  → alternative_doc_finder (scheme_id + missing_doc_type → acceptable_alternatives[])
  → self_declaration_validator (state_code → valid self-declaration formats[])
  → form_generator (citizen profile + scheme_id → pre-filled self-declaration PDF)
  → output: {alternatives[], valid_formats[], pdf_blob}
```

**Agent 10 — Analytics Agent (weekly scheduled):**
```
  → dropoff_analyser (schemes shown vs saved vs applied — MongoDB aggregation)
  → confusion_detector (sessions with repeated questions on same criterion)
  → state_gap_finder (citizen state distribution vs scheme state coverage)
  → benefit_calculator (total estimated benefits unlocked this week)
  → report_generator (Gemini: narrative weekly report from aggregation data)
  → report_storer (admin_reports collection)
  → output: stored weekly report + admin WhatsApp/email notification
```

